snippet.textDisplay:
I remember arguing with people that tried to say Eminem can't be the greatest lyricist rapper of all time. They said Nas was. I said this is my top 5.
1. Eminem.
2. Mos Def.
3. Andre 3000.
4. Masta Ace.
5. Nas.

I look at content, wordplay, and story telling. I look at each word closely and I'll look at unorthodox wordplay too. Eminem has such a hold on lyricism that it's like science. In Killshot, he says "Like the last motherfucker that said Hailey's Name in Vain, Alien Brain". Hailey in vain rhymes with Alien Brain. What he meant was that he was getting so angry that his brain was speeding up out of anger where it was off the charts with flow like an alien brain. Really amazing wordplay
